        },
        {
            "_id": "umjew4vPAU8Ye3xs",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Magnetized Coat",
            "sort": 400000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>When a magnegor comes within 30 feet of a metal object or a deposit of metal ore, its thousands of wiry hairs stand on end, pointing towards the metal and creating a magnetic field. Metal items of light or negligible Bulk that touch the magnegor's coat adhere to it magnetically, requiring an Interact action to be pried free. Creatures wearing or primarily composed of metal treat all squares in a 10-foot radius around the magnegor as difficult terrain, unless they are moving directly towards it.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": []
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "xsHOUZyFnSvFmKSt",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Wallow",
            "sort": 500000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 3
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The magnegor is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Prone]</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The magnegor rolls on its spine-covered back, up to its Speed, furrowing the earth and crushing any Large or smaller creatures in its path. This deals @Damage[4d10[piercing]] damage with a @Check[type:reflex|dc:24|basic:true] save; on a failed save, a creature wearing metal armor or made of metal is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Restrained] by the magnegor's magnetized coat (@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Escape] DC 24). For each metal object or piece of equipment a restrained creature chooses to leave stuck to the magnegor, it gains a +1 circumstance bonus to its attempts to Escape. A creature that relinquishes all its metal Escapes automatically. The magnegor can move at its full Speed while it has a creature restrained in this way, bringing the creature along.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
